source at ===>>>>  https://github.com/joeyschroeder/react-native-simple-animations
npm at =====>>>>>  https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-native-simple-animations

npm install react-native-simple-animations --save

import { SimpleAnimation } from 'react-native-simple-animations';

Use as follows:

<SimpleAnimation delay={500} duration={1000} fade staticType='zoom'>
	<Text>Hello, world!</Text>
</SimpleAnimation>

You can apply the <SimpleAnimation to a single child or multiple childs or to a parent with muliple childs.

Another Example .........

      <TouchableOpacity style = {{marginLeft :window.width - 90,height : 90 ,width :90 }} onPress={() =>  this.props.navigation.navigate('EventList')}>
  <SimpleAnimation style={{}}
    delay={500}
    duration={1000}
    fade
    aim="in"
    staticType='bounce'>
           <View style = {{height : 90 ,width :90 }}>
           <Image style={{marginLeft : 30,marginTop : 30,width :35,height:35 , resizeMode: 'contain'}}
           source={require('./event.png')} />

           <Text style = {{marginTop : 5,textAlign :'center',color :'white',fontSize :20}}>

           Events
           </Text>

           </View>
           </SimpleAnimation>
            </TouchableOpacity>
            
